&lt;p&gt;The 3.0 cqlsh tests are running, I will start the tests on the other branches and move the ticket to patch available when the 3.0 tests are clean.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I noticed that if we set a request timeout, we receive operation-timed-out errors for rows that were already acknowledged, even with the latest driver version (cassandra_test HEAD). Is this a known issue or shall I create a ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aholmber&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aholmber&quot;&gt;aholmber&lt;/a&gt;? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
